Terraform provisioners
provisioners in terraform are used to execute scripts or command after it is created or before it is destructed  

types of provisioners
1)remote-exec  - runs command inside the server  (inline,script,scripts)
2)local-exec  - runs command on local machine
3)files - copy files from local to remote server 


user_data-- is a script that runs automatically when an ec2 instance boots 

Advantages:-
runs when ec2 starts
no ssh required
works in CI/CD 
faster execution
secure


